Doctor Ghost: I finally found him! The Soldier!
Doctor Ghost: I'm so glad I was able to find him, though it seemed like he had forgotten all about me.
Doctor Ghost: I didn't recognize him at first, but the dog tag he had was the one the soldier who saved me had, so it must be them!
Doctor Ghost: He tried to be humble when I thanked him for what he did, but there's no way I could just brush it off!
Doctor Ghost: He was the one who motivated me to keep going! To live for others! If it weren't for him, I would have either died by those enemy soldiers or died from my illness.
Doctor Ghost: I.. I think I'm ready to move on now that I was able to say my thanks.
Doctor Ghost: I'm really glad that this place existed.
Doctor Ghost: Thank you for the drinks. I'm sure that they helped change some people's lives for the better.
